# Q1 — ESG Sustainability Incident Chatbot (Dialogflow CX)

## Overview

This folder contains all evidence for the ESG Sustainability Incident Reporting Chatbot built using Google Dialogflow CX for BUS5001 Assessment 3, Q1.

**Use Case:** Water Leak / Sustainability Incident Reporting  
**Platform:** Google Cloud Dialogflow CX  
**Agent Name:** ESG Sustainability Assistant

---

## What Was Built

### Intents
| Intent | Training Phrases |
|--------|-----------------|
| Report_Water_Leak | 8 training phrases including "There is a water leak", "I want to report a sustainability incident", "Water is coming through the ceiling" |

### Custom Entities
| Entity | Values |
|--------|--------|
| @building | Building A, Building B, Building C |
| @severity | Low, Medium, High, Critical |

### Conversation Pages
| Page | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Start Page | Welcome and incident prompt |
| Location Page | Collects @building parameter |
| Severity Page | Collects @severity — routes Critical to Escalation, others to Description |
| Description Page | Collects free-text @sys.any description |
| Confirmation Page | Confirms submission with reference number |
| Escalation Page | Critical incidents only — notifies Facilities Emergency Team |

### Parameters Configured
- `building` (@building) — required, with re-prompt
- `severity` (@severity) — required, with re-prompt
- `description` (@sys.any) — required, with re-prompt

### Routing Logic
- Location Page → Severity Page (on @building filled)
- Severity Page → Escalation Page (if severity = Critical)
- Severity Page → Description Page (if severity = Low, Medium, or High)
- Description Page → Confirmation Page (on description filled)

